    <section class="section">
      <h1>Application Prototype Overview</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        MealMate is a smart meal planning prototype designed to make weekly planning faster and grocery shopping simpler.
      </p>

      <div class="cards">
        <article class="card">
          <h2>Target Users</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Busy students and working professionals</li>
            <li>Families managing grocery budgets</li>
            <li>Anyone who wants healthier routines</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2>Core Features</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Weekly meal plan builder</li>
            <li>Auto-generated shopping list</li>
            <li>Pantry tracking (what you already have)</li>
            <li>Budget estimate and substitution suggestions</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2>Efficiency Gains</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Less time deciding meals</li>
            <li>Fewer store trips and impulse buys</li>
            <li>Reduced food waste</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Example User Flow</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li>User selects dietary preference and household size.</li>
          <li>User chooses meals for the week (or uses suggested meals).</li>
          <li>App generates a categorized shopping list.</li>
          <li>User checks pantry items to remove duplicates.</li>
          <li>User shops once and cooks from the plan all week.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Prototype Screens (Mock Content)</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          In a real app, these would be images. For this website prototype, we’re showing simple “screen cards.”
        </p>

